  <Name>conversations\03_burninglibrary\03_cv_int01_binder_and_bloodbound</Name>
  <NextEntryID>1</NextEntryID>
  <EntryCount>46</EntryCount>
  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>"It never ends, does it?" The injured Oath Bound soldier laughs ruefully, causing her to cough. Flecks of blood spew from her mouth and hit the cheek of the [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] currently binding her wounds. "Sorry."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>The [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] wipes the blood from his face and makes a dismissive wave with his hand. He immediately returns to binding the Oath Bound's wounds.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What great company, huh?" The Oath Bound smiles with a little wince. "Helpful, handy, and doesn't talk too much. Well...at all. I never did understand what [url=lore:bl_sirin_song]those muzzles[/url] were all about. But, I don't make the hard decisions, do I?" She shrugs and groans again.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You're fine. A little blood comes with the territory. But you need to keep quiet or I won't be able to get this done right. I don't want you bleeding out."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Thank you. I appreciate your help even with all the trouble we've caused you. The Sages aren't nearly as bad as I was led to believe." She smiles and winces.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>She stares at you, all signs of levity gone from her expression. "What are you planning on doing? We are both trapped here with those Chorus members right on the other side of that rubble and I'm certainly in no shape to fight. It would seem we're in quite a bind."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Attack the Oath Bound] "The [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] can live, but the [url=glossary:disfavored]Disfavored[/url] won't fare as well..."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Attack the [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url]] "I'm here to rescue the [url=glossary:disfavored]Disfavored[/url], but the [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] won't be making it out alive..."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Attack them both] "I'm here to finish the job the [url=glossary:scarlet chorus]Scarlet Chorus[/url] obviously weren't able to do..."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Leave] "This is not my concern..."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You have returned. What are your plans?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Please!" The Oath Bound lifts a hand to stop you then yelps in pain. The [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] looks at you, concerned.

"I am in no condition to interfere with whatever you're doing and even if I were, I'm not stupid enough to fight someone here when there are bigger threats."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Wait!" The Oath Bound puts a hand up as well, inhaling sharply in pain. "He is a good man. There is no need to add one more body to the pile. Killing him serves no purpose."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText>The [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url]'s eyes widen with fear and he puts up his hands to stop you.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>That [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] holds up his hands, pleading. "No! Please! I have already seen so many horrors in this library. Don't let my death add to the list. I pose no threat to you!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>17</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You're right. A life spared won't turn the tide. You're not worth killing."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>18</ID>
      <DefaultText>"One [url=glossary:disfavored]Disfavored[/url] soldier left alive is one too many..."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>19</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The soldier is injured, and a Northerner to boot. Let this one go." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>21</ID>
      <DefaultText>The soldier relaxes and slumps back against the shelves. "Thank you. Finding mercy from anyone in here is the last thing I expected."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>22</ID>
      <DefaultText>The [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] visibly relaxes and returns to his work on the Oath Bound.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>23</ID>
      <DefaultText>"One [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] left alive is one too many..."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>24</ID>
      <DefaultText>Both of them visibly relax. The soldier slumps back against the shelves and the [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] returns to his work binding her wounds. "Thank you. Finding mercy from anyone in here is the last thing I expected."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>25</ID>
      <DefaultText>"That was incredibly brutal. But such is the way of war, I suppose."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>27</ID>
      <DefaultText>The [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] looks at you, shocked and wary. "Thank you for sparing my life. It is a shame she had to die, but I will not question your methods. I am just happy to be alive. Though I am still trapped back here because of the Chorus members out there."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>28</ID>
      <DefaultText>The Oath Bound lifts a hand to stop you then yelps in pain.

"I am in no condition to interfere with whatever you're doing and even if I were, I'm not stupid enough to fight someone here when there are bigger threats. And this [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] is a good man. There is no need to add more bodies to the pile. Killing us serves no purpose."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>29</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The soldier is injured, and a Northerner to boot. Let this one go." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>32</ID>
      <DefaultText>"No survivors - those are the rules."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>33</ID>
      <DefaultText>"As soon as I'm able to leave, I will get out of here. The problem is the group over there. Even without this injury, they're going to be difficult to deal with."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>34</ID>
      <DefaultText>"We aren't going anywhere right now, but as soon as I'm ready, I can get us out. The problem is the group over there."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>35</ID>
      <DefaultText>"They're already gone, the way is safe."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>36</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'll let you know when the way is clear."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>39</ID>
      <DefaultText>The [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] holds up his hands in supplication, a terrified look on his face.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>40</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Remove the muzzle from the [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url].]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>43</ID>
      <DefaultText>The [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] holds up his hands in supplication, a terrified look on his face.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>44</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You have returned. What are your plans?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>45</ID>
      <DefaultText>The Oath Bound smiles. "Thank you! As soon as I'm up to it, I will get out of here."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>46</ID>
      <DefaultText>The [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] smiles. "Thank you! As soon as I can, I will get out of here!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>48</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Wait..." She looks at you, recognition showing on her face. "I remember you! You're the Fatebinder that saved my life - all our lives - by [url=lore:bl_chain_of_command]sending the Scarlet Chorus to rescue us![/url]"

"While we escaped, we had to fight some Sages to get out. As far as I know, their bodies are still there. If you find them, I'm sure there are still some magic items or scrolls on them."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>49</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Thank you for your help!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>50</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Thank you for your help!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>51</ID>
      <DefaultText>The Oath Bound smiles. "Thank you! As soon as I'm up to it, I will get out of here."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>53</ID>
      <DefaultText>The [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] smiles. "Thank you! As soon as I can, I will get out of here!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>54</ID>
      <DefaultText>Bank Node 54</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>55</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I've come on behalf of Maric. It's time to go."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>56</ID>
      <DefaultText>The soldier manages a trembling salute, wincing in pain as she does. "Glad to hear it, sir, but as you can see, I've picked up some company." She gives the [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] a worried glance. "This man has aided me and stands to gain nothing from it. I vouch for him, on my life. He won't get in our way."

</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>57</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You're right, another dead [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] won't turn the tide of battle."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
  </Entries>
